JSON -Javascript Object Notation 
    is a lightweight text-based language that helps store data
 JSON is used when exchanging data between a browser and a server, 
 and when generally the data transferred can only be text-based. 
 Since any JavaScript object can be converted into a JSON text, it is essential when dealing with JavaScript.

 key-value pairs are always placed between braces { }

 { 
    "key" : "value",
    "number" : 1,
    "string" : "string value",
    "boolean" : true,
    "array" : [1, 2, "three", true],
    "object" : {"key" : "value"},
    "Null" : null,
}